Field Detail

LOG_EXTENDED_CONTRIBUTION_ID

static final java.lang.String LOG_EXTENDED_CONTRIBUTION_ID
The id for a log contribution. Contributions with this id must have the PROPERTY_NAME_FILE_NAME property and must have the log content stored with setExtendedContributionData. Alternatively, external logs (not stored in the repository), must have the PROPERTY_NAME_URL property to identify the location of the content.

LINK_EXTENDED_CONTRIBUTION_ID

static final java.lang.String LINK_EXTENDED_CONTRIBUTION_ID
The id for a link contribution. Contributions with this id must have the PROPERTY_NAME_URL property.

ARTIFACT_EXTENDED_CONTRIBUTION_ID

static final java.lang.String ARTIFACT_EXTENDED_CONTRIBUTION_ID
The id for an artifact contribution. Artifacts stored in the repository must have the content stored with setExtendedContributionData and must have the PROPERTY_NAME_FILE_NAME property. Alternatively, external artifacts (not stored in the repository), must have the PROPERTY_NAME_URL property to identify the location of the content.

PROPERTY_NAME_URL

static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_NAME_URL
The property name for the URL.

PROPERTY_NAME_FILE_NAME

static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_NAME_FILE_NAME
The property name for the file name. Contains just the file name, not the entire path.

PROPERTY_NAME_FILE_PATH

static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_NAME_FILE_PATH
The property name for the file path. Contains an absolute file path.

PROPERTY_NAME_FILE_SIZE

static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_NAME_FILE_SIZE
The property name for the file size. Property value should be string representation of file size in bytes.

getExtendedContributionProperty

java.lang.String getExtendedContributionProperty(java.lang.String propertyName)

setExtendedContributionProperty

void setExtendedContributionProperty(java.lang.String propertyName,
                                     java.lang.String propertyValue)
Set the extended contribution property value. If the property doesn't exist, it will be created. If the property already exists, the value will be overwritten. This is a convenience method alternative to using getExtendedContributionProperties. If there is more than one property with the given name, the first will be updated.

Parameters:
propertyName - The property name. Must not be null or empty.
propertyValue - The property value. Must not be null or empty.

setStatus

void setStatus(BuildStatus status)
Set the result contribution status. In addition, if the given status is more severe than the containing build result status, and impactsPrimaryResult == true, the containing build result status is also set to the given status. If there is no containing build result, the status is set only on this contribution.

Parameters:
status -

setImpactsPrimaryResult

Set whether this contribution should negatively impact the overall result of the build.

Parameters:
impactsResult - true, if a negative status for this contribution should impact the overall result of the build; false, if this contribution should not impact the overall build result

getComponentName

java.lang.String getComponentName()
Get the component name for the contribution. This is a grouping hint that can be used by UIs to better organize the build contributions. It is optional. It may be a jazz scm component name, but that is not required.

Returns:
The component name. May be empty, but never null.
